<title>ITALY: Olivetti CEO in probe of group statements.</title>
<headline>Olivetti CEO in probe of group statements.</headline>
<dateline>TURIN, Italy 1996-09-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Francesco Caio, the chief executive of crisis-hit Italian information technology group Olivetti, has been put under preliminary investigation by magistrates, judicial sources said on Monday.</p>
<p>The investigation, conducted by magistrates in the town of Ivrea where Olivetti is based, is a first step which could lead to a full-scale criminal investigation into public statements made by Olivetti on its finances.</p>
